## Build knowledge in diversity

Inclusive design helps you to ensure you [Understand users and their needs](/standards/service-standard/1) and that [everyone can use the service](/standards/service-standard/5). 

Do not rely on simulating different abilities for example, using blindfolds, earplugs or putting one hand behind your back, test your service with a wide range of users.

Having empathy for your users and learning how users adapt in different ways to using your service, designers can better understand how to design for a wide range of abilities.

## Solve for one, works for all

Inclusive design means desigining with consideration for many different circumstances. 

However, ensuring your service works for blind users has a knock on effect that it'll all work for users with temporary vision issues using vice over or a screen reader. 

Additionally, someone who might find it easier to listen to guidance or content rather than read it if they are cooking dinner or out for a walk.

